#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:4
msgid "Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:6
msgid ""
"Sending messages and replying to messages are important ways to keep "
"conversations active with your team. You can edit and delete messages "
"after you have sent them. You can also share links to any message in "
"Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:9
msgid "Sending Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:11
msgid ""
"Write a message by typing into the text input box, then press ENTER to "
"send it. Use SHIFT+ENTER to create a new line without sending a message. "
"To send messages by pressing CTRL+ENTER, go to **Main Menu > Account "
"Settings > Advanced > Send messages on Ctrl + Enter > Edit**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:14
msgid "Replying to Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:16
msgid ""
"Click the reply link (arrow icon) next to any message. This keeps "
"conversations organized in threads. Replies are indented slightly in the "
"center pane to indicate that they are child messages of a parent message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:18
msgid ""
"Clicking the reply link will open a sidebar on the right-hand side. To "
"expand the right-hand sidebar to its full width, click the expand/shrink "
"icon with two arrows at the top of the sidebar. To shrink the right-hand "
"sidebar to its original width, click the same expand/shrink icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:21
msgid "Editing Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:23
msgid ""
"Click the **[...]** link next to a message that you have sent, then click"
" **Edit**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:26
msgid ""
"Message edits do not trigger new @mention notifications, desktop "
"notifications, or notification sounds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:28
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Your System Admin `can disable the **Edit** feature or set a time limit "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html?highlight=config%20settings#allow-users-to-edit-their-"
"messages>`__ before messages become uneditable, available in Mattermost "
"Enterprise Edition E10 and E20."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:31
msgid "Deleting Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:33
msgid ""
"Click the **[...]** link next to a message that you have sent, then click"
" **Delete**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:35
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Your System Admin can `disable the **Delete** feature "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html?highlight=config%20settings#allow-which-users-to-delete-"
"messages>`__, available in Mattermost Enterprise Edition E10 and E20."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:38
msgid "Linking to Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:40
msgid ""
"Click the **[...]** link next to a message, then click **Permalink > Copy"
" Link**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:42
msgid ""
"If the link is to a message in a Public Channel, any member of the team "
"can see the message. If the link is to a message in a Private Group, only"
" members in that group can see the message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:45
msgid ""
"The timestamp that appears beside the username of any message is also a "
"permalink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:48
msgid "Marking Messages as Unread"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:50
msgid ""
"Marking a message as unread will bold the channel in your sidebar and add"
" the new messages line above the marked message. This can be a useful "
"reminder to follow-up on the message later if you don't have time to "
"address it when the message was read."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/messaging/sending-messages.rst:52
msgid "Click the **[...]** menu next to a message, then click **Mark as Unread**."
msgstr ""

